6. DUPLICATED errorResponse FUNCTIONS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

5 modules each define their own identical copy of errorResponse:

  1. src/S3OSS/Server.hs:206  (defined locally, hides imports from the other 4)
  2. src/S3OSS/Bucket/Handler.hs:74
  3. src/S3OSS/Object/Handler.hs:104
  4. src/S3OSS/List/Handler.hs:37
  5. src/S3OSS/Multipart/Handler.hs:79

All five are literally identical:

    errorResponse :: Status -> Text -> Text -> Response
    errorResponse status code message =
      responseLBS status
        [("Content-Type", "application/xml")]
        (renderLBS $ renderError code message)

RECOMMENDED OWNER:
  S3OSS.XML is the natural home — it already exports renderLBS and renderError,
  and all handler modules already import it.
  Move errorResponse to src/S3OSS/XML.hs and have Server.hs import from there
  instead of defining its own copy.
  (Task #25 "Centralize errorResponse" is listed as already completed in the task
   tracker, but the actual code still has 5 copies.)

